

British Indian Ocean Territory is a British Overseas Territory. Access is restricted. The British Indian Ocean Territory administration based in London has more information.
Travel insurance
If you are granted permission to travel, research your destinations and get appropriate travel insurance. Insurance should cover your itinerary, planned activities and expenses in an emergency.
About FCDO travel advice
The Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) provides advice about risks of travel to help British nationals make informed decisions. Find out more about FCDO travel advice.
